ack. I was like....What the Frick? &#10;Trust me, a certain percentage are definitely holding back so their kid can be the oldest. They won't TELL you that is why - they will say something random about their child's maturity or benefitting from an extra year, but it IS because they don't want their snowflake to be the youngest one. &#10;Again, I've been pretty clear that I know kids that were correctly redshirted. No one disputes that. But if you've made the decision at age of 8 months that you are going to do it, I call foul on your reasoning. "/><type4:DocumentMetaData xmi:id="13" sofa="1" begin="0" end="850" language="en" documentId="5203" isLastSegment="false"/><types:WebArgumentMetadata xmi:id="24" sofa="1" begin="0" end="0" author="Bigmouthstrikesagain" date="04/05/2012" docType="forumpost" origUrl="http://community.babycenter.com/post/a32503567/yet_another_redshirting_debate?cpg=17" topic="redshirting" thumbsUp="0" thumbsDown="0" origId="5203" notes="" title="Yet another redshirting debate"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="39" sofa="1" begin="0" end="342"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="43" sofa="1" begin="343" end="637"/><type6:Paragraph xmi:id="47" sofa="1" begin="638" end="850"/><cas:View sofa="1" members="13 24 39 43 47"/></xmi:XMI>